  "text": "The Node.js ESM (ECMAScript Module) loader and CJS-ESM interop bridge consists of several interconnected layers:\n\n## Entry Point Detection and Main Execution\n\nThe entry point for ESM/CJS module loading detection begins in `lib/internal/modules/run_main.js`. The `executeUserEntryPoint()` function determines whether to use the ESM loader based on file extensions (.mjs), package.json type field, or explicit --experimental-default-type flag. The `runEntryPointWithESMLoader()` function initializes the ESM loader and executes user imports before running the entry point, with `asyncRunEntryPointWithESMLoader()` handling the actual async execution.\n\n## ModuleLoader Class and Core Loader\n\nThe central component is the `ModuleLoader` class in `lib/internal/modules/esm/loader.js` (lines 110+). This class manages:\n- Resolution cache (#resolveCache) using ResolveCache from module_map.js\n- Load cache (loadCache) using LoadCache from module_map.js  \n- Module translators using translators from translators.js\n- Customizations for loader hooks\n- Import metadata initialization\n- Module resolution and loading through the resolve/load/translate pipeline\n\nThe `createModuleLoader()` function (lines 801+) instantiates the loader, and `getOrInitializeCascadedLoader()` provides a singleton instance for cascaded loader chain support.\n\n## Module Job Pipeline and Linking\n\n`ModuleJob` class in `lib/internal/modules/esm/module_job.js` (lines 72+) represents a single module's loading state with:\n- ModuleWrap binding from the C++ module\n- Module promise for async compilation\n- Linking pipeline (_link method, line 100+) that processes dependencies\n- Evaluation pipeline (_evaluate method) for executing module code\n- Support for both source text modules and synthetic modules\n\nThe linking phase connects all module dependencies recursively before evaluation.\n\n## Module Resolution\n\n`lib/internal/modules/esm/resolve.js` contains the resolution algorithm:\n- `defaultResolve()` function performs standard module specifier resolution\n- Package.json exports/imports resolution using `packageExportsResolve()` and `packageImportsResolve()`\n- URL-based resolution for file://, data:, and node: protocol URLs\n- Import attributes (formerly assertions) validation\n- Specifier normalization and package boundary detection\n\n## CJS-ESM Interop Bridge\n\n`lib/internal/modules/cjs/loader.js` implements the ESM fallback for CommonJS:\n- `finalizeEsmResolution()` function (line 1258) bridges CJS module loading with ESM resolution\n- Uses packageExportsResolve and packageImportsResolve from esm/resolve.js for package exports in CommonJS context\n- Enables require() in CommonJS modules to resolve ESM package exports\n- CJS loader integration at module._compile() for ESM-compatible module loading\n\n## Module Format Detection and Translation\n\n`lib/internal/modules/esm/get_format.js` provides format detection:\n- `defaultGetFormat()` function (line 240+) determines module format from file extension and content\n- Supports 'module', 'commonjs', 'json', 'wasm', and 'builtin' formats\n- Handles .mjs, .cjs, .js, .json file extensions with package.json type field support\n\n`lib/internal/modules/esm/formats.js` defines format metadata:\n- Extension to format mapping (extensionFormatMap)\n- MIME type to format mapping (mimeToFormat)\n- Format validation for import attributes\n- Wasm module support detection\n\n`lib/internal/modules/esm/translators.js` (lines 97+) translates modules into ModuleWrap objects:\n- 'module' translator for JavaScript ES modules (line 97)\n- 'commonjs' translator for CJS modules using cjs-module-lexer\n- 'json' translator for JSON files\n- 'wasm' translator for WebAssembly modules\n- 'builtin' translator for Node.js built-in modules\n- Each translator produces a ModuleWrap via ModuleJob\n\n## Module Loading Pipeline\n\n`lib/internal/modules/esm/load.js` implements the load hook:\n- `defaultLoad()` function (line 87) fetches source code\n- `getSource()` async function for file:// and data: protocol URLs\n- `getSourceSync()` function for synchronous loading\n- Integration with source map caching\n\n## Loader Hooks and Customization\n\n`lib/internal/modules/esm/hooks.js` provides:\n- `HooksProxy` class for communicating with custom loader code in a worker thread\n- resolve and load hook processing with import attribute handling\n- Loader chaining support for multiple custom loaders\n- Worker thread isolation for custom hooks\n- Error deserialization for hook failures\n\n## Module Caching\n\n`lib/internal/modules/esm/module_map.js`:\n- `ResolveCache` class caches resolution results by (specifier, parentURL, importAttributes) tuple\n- `LoadCache` class caches loaded modules by (url, format) pair\n- Implements caching required by TC39 spec for consistent module identity\n\n## Import Metadata and Dynamic Modules\n\n`lib/internal/modules/esm/initialize_import_meta.js` initializes import.meta object with:\n- url property for module URL\n- resolve() method for import.meta.resolve()\n- Integration with ModuleLoader for resolution context\n\n`lib/internal/modules/esm/create_dynamic_module.js` creates synthetic modules for:\n- Programmatically created modules (e.g., JSON, WASM)\n- CJS facade modules for CommonJS compatibility\n- Dynamic imports of non-JavaScript formats\n\n## Utilities and Supporting Infrastructure\n\n`lib/internal/modules/esm/utils.js`:\n- `initializeESM()` function sets up ESM infrastructure\n- `getDefaultConditions()` returns export field resolution conditions\n- `getConditionsSet()` manages condition validation\n- Defines loaderWorkerId for custom loader identification\n\n`lib/internal/modules/esm/assert.js` validates import attributes:\n- Attribute-format compatibility checking\n- kImplicitTypeAttribute constant for formats without required type\n\n`lib/internal/modules/esm/shared_constants.js` defines worker communication constants:\n- SHARED_MEMORY_BYTE_LENGTH for inter-thread coordination\n- WORKER_TO_MAIN_THREAD_NOTIFICATION for signaling\n\n`lib/internal/modules/esm/worker.js` implements the hooks worker thread:\n- Receives hook requests from main thread\n- Executes resolve/load/globalPreload hooks\n- Returns results or error information\n\n## Native C++ Bindings\n\n`src/module_wrap.h` defines the ModuleWrap C++ class:\n- Wraps v8::Module (JavaScript module object)\n- Internal fields for module, URL, context, and synthetic evaluation steps\n- Methods for compilation (CompileSourceTextModule), linking (Link), and evaluation (Evaluate)\n- Host-defined options for module identity\n- Memory tracking and garbage collection support\n\n`src/module_wrap.cc` implements ModuleWrap:\n- Constructor binds module to V8 isolate and environment\n- Weak reference handling for garbage collection\n- GetFromModule() to retrieve ModuleWrap from v8::Module\n- Module import/export handling\n- Top-level await detection for process exit handling\n- Host initialize import.meta callback support\n\n`src/env.h` declares environment-level module tracking:\n- hash_to_module_map for quick module lookup by identity hash\n- Host callbacks for import.meta initialization and dynamic import\n\n`src/env.cc` manages module callbacks and environment state for ESM execution.\n\n`src/node_modules.h` and `src/node_modules.cc` implement PackageConfig:\n- Package.json parsing using simdjson\n- Export field resolution logic\n- Version validation and error handling\n\n`src/node_contextify.cc` integrates modules with V8 contexts:\n- CompileSourceTextModule compilation with code caching\n- HostDefinedOptions creation for module identity\n- Context-specific module compilation\n\n## Bootstrap and Realm Integration\n\n`lib/internal/bootstrap/realm.js` initializes realm-level module infrastructure:\n- ModuleWrap binding registration\n- Realm context setup for module execution\n- Module namespace object creation\n\n`lib/internal/vm/module.js` provides the public SourceTextModule and SyntheticModule APIs:\n- Wrapper around ModuleWrap for user code\n- Link and evaluate methods for the module lifecycle\n\n## CJS-ESM Shared Utilities\n\n`lib/internal/modules/helpers.js` provides shared utilities:\n- URL-filename conversion for cross-loader compatibility\n- Real path resolution and symlink handling\n- Module source and export detection\n\n`lib/internal/modules/package_json_reader.js` provides package.json caching:\n- Shared cache between ESM and CJS loaders\n- Efficient lookups for package.json type and exports fields\n\nThis comprehensive architecture enables Node.js to seamlessly load both ESM and CJS modules, resolve package exports across both systems, support custom loader hooks, and maintain full backward compatibility while providing modern module features."
